The [[2010 United States census]]<ref name="Census 2010">{{cite web| url=http://factfinder2.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/G001/1600000US3236500| title=Geographic Identifiers: 2010 Demographic Profile Data (G001): Jackpot CDP, Nevada| publisher=U.S. Census Bureau, American Factfinder| access-date=February 16, 2016}}{{dead link|bot=medic|date=April 2020}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> reported that Jackpot had a population of 1,195. The racial makeup of Jackpot was 61% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]] (41% Non-Hispanic White),<ref>{{cite web |url=http://quickfacts.census.gov/qfd/states/06/0624477.html |title=Florence-Graham CDP QuickFacts from the US Census Bureau |access-date=2012-09-08 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120702005752/http://quickfacts.census.gov/qfd/states/06/0624477.html |archive-date=2012-07-02 }}</ref> 1% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 32% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 4% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 56%.

There were 451 households, out of which 33% had children under the age of 18 living in them. The average household size was 2.65. There were 266 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (59% of all households); the average family size was 3.60.

The population was spread out, with 31% under the age of 18 and 9% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 34.2 years.

There were 622 housing units, of which 28% were vacant. Of the occupied units, 36% were owner-occupied and 65% were rented.

The median household income was $39,926, with 15% of the population living below the federal poverty line.

